# Vkraynosti Project Rules

## Architecture
- SPA with React + TypeScript + Vite + Tailwind CSS v3
- React Router v7 for routing
- All pages live in src/pages/, all components in src/components/
- Global state via React Context only (no Redux)
- Data layer: src/data/*.ts — all tour/team/safety data as typed constants

## No Hardcode Policy (CRITICAL)
- NEVER hardcode colors, font sizes, spacing, z-index, breakpoints inline
- ALL design tokens defined in tailwind.config.ts under `theme.extend`
- ALL text content (names, descriptions, labels) comes from src/data/*.ts or src/constants/ui.ts
- ALL image paths defined in src/constants/images.ts as named exports
- ALL route paths defined in src/constants/routes.ts
- ALL external links (phone, telegram, max) defined in src/constants/contacts.ts

## Component Rules
- Every component receives typed props — no `any`
- No logic in JSX — extract to hooks or helpers
- Modal state managed in src/context/ModalContext.tsx
- Carousel logic extracted to src/hooks/useCarousel.ts
- All icons from FontAwesome via @fortawesome/react-fontawesome

## Tailwind Rules
- Use only classes defined in tailwind.config.ts custom theme
- Responsive: mobile-first, breakpoints: sm(640) md(768) lg(1024) xl(1280)
- Dark sections use bg-surface-dark, light sections use bg-surface-light
- Animations defined in tailwind.config.ts keyframes section

## File Naming
- Components: PascalCase (HeroCarousel.tsx)
- Hooks: camelCase with use prefix (useCarousel.ts)
- Data files: camelCase (toursData.ts)
- Constants: camelCase (routes.ts)

## Commit Checkpoints
After each phase, verify: TypeScript compiles, no console errors, routing works, no hardcoded values remain.

## Tech Notes
- React 19: Use functional components with hooks; Context + useReducer for state; createPortal for modals
- React Router v7: createBrowserRouter with nested routes and Layout outlet; useParams for dynamic segments
- Tailwind CSS v3: All custom tokens in theme.extend; use @layer components for reusable classes; content paths must include ./src/**/*.{ts,tsx}
- FontAwesome React: Install @fortawesome/react-fontawesome + icon packs; import { FontAwesomeIcon } from '@fortawesome/react-fontawesome'; use library.add() or direct icon imports
- Vite: Fast HMR dev server; env vars via import.meta.env; build output to dist/
- TypeScript: Strict interfaces for all data shapes; use `as const` for constant objects; avoid `any` — use `unknown` + type guards instead
